12 'Sec. 1. Transfer of real estate transfer tax revenue. Notwithstanding the
13 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 36, section 4641-B, subsection 4-B, paragraphs E-1 and E-3,
14 for fiscal year 2025-26 only, prior to the transfer pursuant to Title 36, section 4641-B,
15 subsection 4-B, paragraph E-3, the State Controller shall first credit $2,982,000 of the
16 revenues available to the Maine State Housing Authority for the Housing Opportunities for
17 Maine Fund established in Title 30-A, section 4853 and $1,491,000 of the revenue available
18 to the Department of Health and Human Services for the Housing First Fund established in
19 Title 22, section 20-A, subsection 2 to the General Fund.
